Boko Haram militants have released the first images of their activities since pledging allegiance to ISIS leader Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi . 
  Images show jihadis casually posing in front of the terror group's sinister black and white flag while brandishing assault rifles . 
  Comes as Nigerian soldiers retreat from last known stronghold in the Sambisa forest . 
  Earlier this year the group pledged allegiance to the ISIS leader in a video . 
  The images suggest the militants have taken full control of Boko Haram propaganda . 
 